{
  "stem": "7506.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were told to form into a column, with five in a row, five people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we had to carry our luggage, the stuff we had, which was the rucksack.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I had no suitcases.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I personally, my family had just a rucksack and the thing over our arm.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we were marched off the siding.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And eventually what we later learned to be Bergen-Belsen, the camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Known as Belsen, but its proper name is Bergen-Belsen, because the little village it's near is called Bergen, which is in a part of Germany, which is on the Luneburger Heide, in the Northwest part of Germany, between Hanover and Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It's a part of Niedersachsen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And the provincial capital there is Celle, C-E-L-L-E.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But the camp was outside of Bergen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "That's why it's called Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we got to the camp, they opened the gates, which was barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we stopped once we were inside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We stopped at a barrack.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And like two by two the people went into the barrack.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And outside the door of the barrack was a German SS.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had to walk up two steps to go into the barrack.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And everybody went into that barrack and came out the other side.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Eventually, I had to go with my father into the barrack.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember, at that time, I think it was the first time I was physically touched, where the German soldier pushed his rifle in my side-- I mean, I was only like this big-- to put my hands up.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that way we stepped up the steps inside.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Looking at it now, thinking about it, whether it was to show that we didn't have anything in our hands, I just don't know.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
